President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation recognizing National Defense Transportation Day and National Transportation Week. In the proclamation, he emphasized the importance of a strong transportation infrastructure system for economic strength, national defense, and the American way of life. He highlighted the deteriorating state of the nation's infrastructure, including structurally deficient bridges, poor road conditions, and congestion. President Trump called on Congress to pass legislation to fund the rebuilding of roads and bridges, with a focus on rural communities. He also emphasized the need for regulatory reform to expedite infrastructure projects. Lastly, he emphasized that maintaining and improving infrastructure is crucial for economic and national security, as it supports manufacturing, emergency responses, energy independence, and military readiness. The proclamation encourages Americans to celebrate these observances and recognize the contributions of the transportation industry to the nation's well-being and defense.